.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATETIME.TOPLAINTIME" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDateTime.toPlainTime \-
Temporal.PlainDateTime.prototype.toPlainTime()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]toPlainTime()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDateTime\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] object representing the time part (hour,
minute, second, and subsecond components) of this date\-time.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
toPlainTime()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] object representing the time part
(hour, minute, second, and subsecond components) of this date\-time.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using toPlainTime()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dt = Temporal.PlainDateTime.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01T12:34:56\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] time = dt.toPlainTime();
console.log(time.toString()); \f[I]// \(aq12:34:56\(aq\f[R]
.EE
